Senator Gbenga Ashafa, lawmaker representing Lagos East Senatorial District in the National Assembly has expressed confidence in Musiliu Smith, former Inspector General of Police to bring about the necessary reforms needed to transform the Nigeria Police Service Commission. He made this statement in his address during the consideration of the report of the Committee on Police Affairs confirming the appointment of  Smith as the Chairman of the Police Service Commission. Ashafa, the Chairman Senate Committee on Land Transport said  “Former IGP Musiliu Smith is renowned to have conducted himself professionally at all his duty posts which endeared him to all law abiding members of the various communities where he served and indeed the entire Nation while he served as the Inspector General of Police between 1999 and 2002. “I am confident that he will bring his professionalism to bear on his new appointment and thereby ensure that the necessary reforms are instituted in the Nigerian Police Service Commission” The Senator also encouraged the rank and file of the police to remain enthusiastic and support the new PSC boss saying  Smith would continue to put their welfare and regularize the promotion scale of the entire force. Smith upon his confirmation by the Senate today 17th July, 2018 is to replace former IGP Mike Okiro as the Chairman of the Police Service Commission. comments Do you get a good or bad response from your wife after making love? Discover a great natural solution that changed my story and put an end to weak/premature ejaculation, CLICK HERE. 